<article id="post-2879" class="post-2879 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-children category-family category-general tag-birthday tag-dearchoochoo">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2011/03/happy-first-birthday-choo-choo/" rel="bookmark">Happy first birthday, Choo Choo!</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<a class="post-thumbnail" href="http://geoff.wp/2011/03/happy-first-birthday-choo-choo/" aria-hidden="true">
			</a>

		
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Well, my little girl, you&#8217;re a year old today. A year ago, <a title="Arrived: Choo Choo" href="http://www.sowrey.org/2010/03/arrived-choo-choo/">you came into our world early, confused, cold, and separated from Mommy</a>. It wasn&#8217;t exactly how any of us had hoped you&#8217;d arrive, but we were happy to have you no matter how it all went.<br />
Mommy and I had been looking forward to today for a long time. We wanted your first birthday to be small, surrounded with just a few of us, making as much fuss as we could without completely overwhelming you. Today wasn&#8217;t really about you, so much as it was about us. You see, we&#8217;re actually kind of sad, today.<br />
Why? Well, you&#8217;re no longer our baby girl. You&#8217;re grown up.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2011/03/happy-first-birthday-choo-choo/#more-2879" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Happy first birthday, Choo Choo!&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
