<article id="post-2717" class="post-2717 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-children category-family category-general category-travel tag-dearchoochoo tag-dearmonkey tag-manitoba tag-roadtrip tag-saskatchewan tag-winnipeg">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/08/the-great-family-roadtrip-2010-day-3/" rel="bookmark">The Great Family Roadtrip 2010, Day 3</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>At least we didn&#8217;t have to get up too early today, Choo Choo, and you let us sleep a bit longer. That helped rest away the many kilometres behind us. We hit breakfast, also at the Chicken Chef (there ain&#8217;t a lot of option in Whitewood), and then loaded up once more for our push to Winnipeg.<br />
It took a lot longer than I thought to get here.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/08/the-great-family-roadtrip-2010-day-3/#more-2717" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;The Great Family Roadtrip 2010, Day 3&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
