<article id="post-2716" class="post-2716 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-children category-family category-general category-travel tag-dearchoochoo tag-dearmonkey tag-manitoba tag-roadtrip tag-saskatchewan tag-winnipeg">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/08/the-great-family-roadtrip-2010-day-2/" rel="bookmark">The Great Family Roadtrip 2010, Day 2</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Choo Choo, I don&#8217;t think you yet have a real understanding of time. And certainly, you don&#8217;t understand the idea of letting Mommy or Daddy sleep in. Today, I&#8217;ll admit, that wasn&#8217;t something we would fault you for, since we all had to be up early. Grandpa wanted us on the road by 7:00. That meant getting up, dressed, fed, packed, and loaded.<br />
And as Mommy and I have noticed, neither you nor your sister, Monkey, really understand the idea of &#8220;quickly&#8221;.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/08/the-great-family-roadtrip-2010-day-2/#more-2716" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;The Great Family Roadtrip 2010, Day 2&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
